SECTION 1 Subject of Agreement. "Product", as referred to in this Agreement,
shall be the Open Data Hadrian Scoring Engine source code and/or JAR binary
software package ("Hadrian").    Hadrian allows for the building and consuming
of predictive and statistical models adhering to the PFA specification. The
Product consists of source code and executable files for use within a Java
Virtual Machine, as well as other data files as required by the executable files
at run-time and documentation in electronic form. The Product includes all
documentation and updates provided to You by Open Data under this Agreement and
the terms of this Agreement will apply to all such documentation and updates
unless a different license is provided with an update or documentation.

SECTION 2 Grant of license. (1) Open Data grants you a personal, non-exclusive,
non-transferable, limited license without fees to reproduce, install, execute,
and use internally the Product for your Personal Use, Academic Use, Educational
Use, or Evaluation. "Personal Use" requires that you use the Product on the same
computer where you installed it yourself. "Educational use" is any use in an
educational institution (schools, colleges and universities, by teachers and
students).  "Academic use" is use in any academic institution for research use.
"Evaluation" means testing the Product for a reasonable period (that is,
normally for a few weeks); after expiry of that term, you are no longer
permitted to evaluate the Product.

